00:13:52.681 --> 00:13:56.018
Death is such a natural.
necessary part of life.

254
00:13:56.143 --> 00:13:58.687
Every second.
millions of cells die.

255
00:13:58.812 --> 00:14:01.272
shedding diseased
parts of ourselves

256
00:14:01.273 --> 00:14:03.442
to make room for new cells.

257
00:14:03.567 --> 00:14:05.861
Rebirth. Growth.

258
00:14:05.986 --> 00:14:07.904
Life.

259
00:14:07.905 --> 00:14:12.034
A million little deaths
that keep us healthy.

260
00:14:13.410 --> 00:14:15.037
This was the New York Ripper's.

261
00:14:15.162 --> 00:14:16.329
A man who terrorized

262
00:14:16.330 --> 00:14:19.081
the streets I once
played on as a child.

263
00:14:19.082 --> 00:14:21.293
Highly prolific.

264
00:14:21.418 --> 00:14:22.335
Never caught.

265
00:14:22.336 --> 00:14:23.795
<i>Must be nice.</i>

266
00:14:24.671 --> 00:14:25.756
<i>This memorabilia.</i>

267
00:14:25.881 --> 00:14:27.299
<i>these trophies.</i>

268
00:14:28.592 --> 00:14:30.886
<i>Harry would have
found it disgusting.</i>

269
00:14:32.054 --> 00:14:33.304
<i>But here. they're celebrated.</i>

270
00:14:33.305 --> 00:14:35.641
[Prater]
Arthur Mitchell.

271
00:14:36.516 --> 00:14:38.936
The infamous Trinity Killer.

272
00:14:41.396 --> 00:14:44.524
<i>♪ Oh. Venus ♪</i>

273
00:14:45.734 --> 00:14:47.902
Which was actually a misnomer.
Did you know that

274
00:14:47.903 --> 00:14:50.155
- he killed in fours?
- [Dexter] <i>Killed in fours.</i>

275
00:14:50.280 --> 00:14:51.448
You don't say?

276
00:14:53.659 --> 00:14:57.621
Bought those from an FBI agent
with a gambling problem.

277
00:14:57.746 --> 00:15:00.165
♪ dramatic music ♪

278
00:15:08.006 --> 00:15:10.258
<i>I've missed you. friends.</i>

279
00:15:10.259 --> 00:15:12.386
- Please don't touch.
- Sorry.

280
00:15:14.096 --> 00:15:16.181
[laughs]

281
00:15:18.517 --> 00:15:19.977
It's quite a collection.

282
00:15:20.102 --> 00:15:22.353
An ever-expanding collection.

283
00:15:22.354 --> 00:15:25.315
That is the table
where the Ice Truck Killer

284
00:15:25.440 --> 00:15:27.401
took his own life.

285
00:15:42.165 --> 00:15:43.667
Tragic. I know.

286
00:15:44.835 --> 00:15:47.128
Maybe if Brian Moser
had someone to talk to.

287
00:15:47.129 --> 00:15:51.008
someone like himself.
he would still be with us today.

288
00:15:54.052 --> 00:15:55.178
[crying]

289
00:15:55.304 --> 00:15:57.556
<i>Doubtful.</i>

290
00:16:00.517 --> 00:16:04.062
A gift from
one of my guests. Rapunzel.

291
00:16:07.232 --> 00:16:09.066
- You'll meet him tonight.
- [Dexter] <i>Great. I get to</i>

292
00:16:09.067 --> 00:16:11.402
<i>- meet ponytail guy.</i>
- And over here

293
00:16:11.403 --> 00:16:13.655
is someone else
you'll meet tonight.

294
00:16:15.490 --> 00:16:17.950
- Is that...
- Severed tattoo sleeve

295
00:16:17.951 --> 00:16:19.828
from the Tattoo Collector.

296
00:16:22.789 --> 00:16:26.710
I've set aside a spot for you.

297
00:16:26.835 --> 00:16:31.506
That is. if you're willing
to part with a trophy.

298
00:16:31.631 --> 00:16:33.467
Right.

299
00:16:34.301 --> 00:16:35.802
The trophy.

300
00:16:51.860 --> 00:16:53.528
[Prater]
Tyler Day.

301
00:16:55.072 --> 00:16:57.115
Your first.

302
00:16:58.492 --> 00:17:00.369
I am honored.

303
00:17:09.961 --> 00:17:13.506
I'm surprised you keep
all this evidence around.

304
00:17:13.507 --> 00:17:16.175
Are all your other guests
okay with it?

305
00:17:16.176 --> 00:17:18.512
They trust me.

306
00:17:18.637 --> 00:17:20.471
And five inches

307
00:17:20.472 --> 00:17:23.183
of solid steel
behind this limestone.

308
00:17:23.308 --> 00:17:25.602
And if anyone were to

309
00:17:25.727 --> 00:17:26.978
put in the wrong code.

310
00:17:27.104 --> 00:17:28.772
- just once...
- [keypad beeping]

311
00:17:29.773 --> 00:17:31.650
[alarm blaring]

312
00:17:32.734 --> 00:17:33.734
[gun cocks]

313
00:17:33.735 --> 00:17:34.860
[Prater]
Charley will take care

314
00:17:34.861 --> 00:17:36.488
