- [Mia] I kind of do too.

504
00:24:57.679 --> 00:24:59.012
[Lowell]
Nice to see you. buddy.

505
00:24:59.013 --> 00:25:00.807
- [Al] It is...
- Excuse me.

506
00:25:00.932 --> 00:25:02.474
- [Al] Yeah.
- Please.

507
00:25:02.475 --> 00:25:04.686
[Al]
Really cuts to the chase.

508
00:25:05.812 --> 00:25:08.063
It's nice to be able to talk
freely. you know what I mean?

509
00:25:08.064 --> 00:25:09.898
Well. it felt good
to hear it out loud.

510
00:25:09.899 --> 00:25:11.400
[conversation continues
indistinctly]

511
00:25:11.401 --> 00:25:12.944
[Harry] If I didn't
know any better. I'd think

512
00:25:13.069 --> 00:25:15.655
I was watching
some kind of boogeyman club.

513
00:25:16.447 --> 00:25:17.906
You're still gonna
kill these guys. right?

514
00:25:17.907 --> 00:25:19.450
I don't even have
concrete proof.

515
00:25:19.576 --> 00:25:21.870
Remember that whole Code thing
you taught me?

516
00:25:21.995 --> 00:25:25.164
I also taught you
not to play with your food.

517
00:25:25.957 --> 00:25:27.834
Dinner is served.

518
00:25:29.002 --> 00:25:31.087
- [Lowell] Let's roll.
- [Mia] Wonderful.

519
00:25:31.212 --> 00:25:32.796
[Al]
Hey. sit by me. sit by me.

520
00:25:32.797 --> 00:25:34.799
- Do we know what's on the menu?
- Yes.

521
00:25:34.924 --> 00:25:37.135
♪ classical piano music ♪

522
00:25:41.973 --> 00:25:43.850
- This'll do.
- Nice. look at this.

523
00:25:43.975 --> 00:25:45.143
[whoops]

524
00:25:48.688 --> 00:25:50.356
Is. uh. Keith coming?

525
00:25:50.773 --> 00:25:52.983
He won't be joining us.

526
00:25:52.984 --> 00:25:54.360
[grunts]

527
00:25:55.653 --> 00:25:57.864
[Prater]
We have one rule here.

528
00:25:59.741 --> 00:26:01.159
Never turn on the group.

529
00:26:01.993 --> 00:26:05.204
Unfortunately.
Keith chose not to abide by it.

530
00:26:05.997 --> 00:26:08.708
My rules are made
for your safety.

531
00:26:08.833 --> 00:26:10.710
not your punishment.

532
00:26:13.963 --> 00:26:17.717
The Canton Clubber's bat
will join my collection.

533
00:26:19.844 --> 00:26:22.555
As he no longer has
any use for it.

534
00:26:26.726 --> 00:26:29.646
[Dexter] <i>Huh.
So. this buffet can bite back.</i>

535
00:26:29.771 --> 00:26:31.480
[Prater]
But on the bright side.

536
00:26:31.481 --> 00:26:33.357
we still have

537
00:26:33.358 --> 00:26:35.443
so much to be thankful for.

538
00:26:35.568 --> 00:26:37.737
Welcome. Red.

539
00:26:38.863 --> 00:26:40.949
We're so grateful
to have you here.

540
00:26:43.201 --> 00:26:44.702
To new friends.

541
00:26:45.411 --> 00:26:46.371
- [all assenting]
- To new friends.

542
00:26:46.496 --> 00:26:48.039
To new friends.

543
00:26:50.249 --> 00:26:52.460
Thank you for letting me in.

544
00:26:54.963 --> 00:26:57.798
[Al] All right. let's eat
before these get... get cold.

545
00:26:57.799 --> 00:27:00.842
I guess we. uh.
each just take one?

546
00:27:00.843 --> 00:27:03.137
- Stern. or...
- [Mia] Okay.

547
00:27:05.723 --> 00:27:07.224
[Lowell]
Would you like some salad?

548
00:27:07.225 --> 00:27:08.559
[Prater clears throat]

549
00:27:08.685 --> 00:27:10.395
- [Al] Oh. rosemary.
- [Lowell] Mmm. mmm. mmm.

550
00:27:11.229 --> 00:27:13.355
[Prater]
Pan-seared cauliflower.

551
00:27:13.356 --> 00:27:16.526
With Japanese turnip medallions

552
00:27:17.485 --> 00:27:19.861
in a sweet potato puree.

553
00:27:19.862 --> 00:27:21.446
Charley found the vegan products

554
00:27:21.447 --> 00:27:23.616
and cookbooks in your apartment.

555
00:27:23.741 --> 00:27:25.575
- Oh.
- Good news.

556
00:27:25.576 --> 00:27:27.870
There's more
where that came from.

557
00:27:29.872 --> 00:27:31.499
[Lowell]
I'm glad I didn't have lunch.

558
00:27:31.624 --> 00:27:33.250
These are prime for sure.
no doubt.

559
00:27:33.251 --> 00:27:35.753
["The Four Seasons: Winter"
by Vivaldi playing on speakers]

560
00:27:48.433 --> 00:27:49.642
What's happening?

561
00:27:49.767 --> 00:27:52.061
Time for the highlight
of the evening.

562
00:27:52.186 --> 00:27:53.603
Take it away. Lowell.

563
00:27:53.604 --> 00:27:55.857
Let's show and tell. baby.

564
00:27:56.858 --> 00:27:58.734
So I wanted to try something new

565
00:27:58.735 --> 00:28:00.736
this go-around. something fun.

566
00:28:00.737 --> 00:28:02.487
So I've put together
a little multimedia

567
00:28:02.488 --> 00:28:03.740
presentation for y'all.

568
00:28:03.865 --> 00:28:05.365
[Dexter]
<i>Oh. no. are we about to watch</i>

569
00:28:05.366 --> 00:28:06.659
<i>a vacation slideshow?</i>

570
00:28:06.784 --> 00:28:08.910
If he plays
a vacation slideshow.

571
00:28:08.911 --> 00:28:11.621
permission
to light myself on fire.

572
00:28:11.622 --> 00:28:13.833
[Lowell] So tonight
I'm letting you all in

573
00:28:13.958 --> 00:28:15.376
on my process.

574
00:28:15.501 --> 00:28:17.754
As most of you know.
I've always had

575
00:28:17.879 --> 00:28:20.255
a deep connection to tattoos.

576
00:28:20.256 --> 00:28:21.673
Yeah. he does. [chuckles]

577
00:28:21.674 --> 00:28:23.258
[Lowell]
And lately.

578
00:28:23.259 --> 00:28:24.802
this artist has been

579
00:28:24.927 --> 00:28:27.847
doing some real
interesting work.

580
00:28:27.972 --> 00:28:29.474
See. it's about

581
00:28:29.599 --> 00:28:31.224
the right piece

582
00:28:31.225 --> 00:28:33.351
on the right person.

583
00:28:33.352 --> 00:28:35.646
♪ menacing music ♪

584
00:28:37.106 --> 00:28:38.815
This is Jules.

585
00:28:38.816 --> 00:28:41.152
I've been following her journey

586
00:28:41.277 --> 00:28:43.029
for weeks now.

587
00:28:43.821 --> 00:28:45.865
If this motherfucker
ever tried his shit on me.

588
00:28:45.990 --> 00:28:49.660
I would make him eat
his own eyeballs.

589
00:28:49.786 --> 00:28:51.746
[Lowell]
Her...

590
00:28:51.871 --> 00:28:53.539
15-year-old dog

591
00:28:53.664 --> 00:28:54.581
recently passed.

592
00:28:54.582 --> 00:28:56.042
Aw. poor pooch.

593
00:28:56.167 --> 00:28:57.667
And so Jules...

594
00:28:57.668 --> 00:29:00.588
decided to get some new ink

595
00:29:00.713 --> 00:29:02.548
in his memory.

596
00:29:06.302 --> 00:29:07.928
[gasps] Wow.

597
00:29:07.929 --> 00:29:09.679
[Dexter]
<i>Internet stalking?</i>

598
00:29:09.680 --> 00:29:12.099
<i>Back in my day you had
to actually leave the house.</i>

599
00:29:12.100 --> 00:29:15.018
[Lowell]
I knew this was my next piece

600
00:29:15.019 --> 00:29:17.355
the moment I laid eyes on it.

601
00:29:19.482 --> 00:29:21.567
And what happens next...

602
00:29:23.027 --> 00:29:24.946
...is inevitable.

603
00:29:26.656 --> 00:29:28.157
"Inevitable"?

604
00:29:28.282 --> 00:29:30.576
Because I can't stop it.

605
00:29:31.828 --> 00:29:34.330
I feel the pressure rise.

606
00:29:34.455 --> 00:29:36.249
becomes so intense...

607
00:29:37.834 --> 00:29:39.710
...it's dizzying...

608
00:29:40.545 --> 00:29:43.046
...unstoppable.

609
00:29:43.047 --> 00:29:45.424
[Dexter]
<i>I know the feeling.</i>

610
00:29:45.550 --> 00:29:47.343
I call it "the Itch."

611
00:29:47.468 --> 00:29:48.803
"The Need."

612
00:29:48.928 --> 00:29:51.222
"The Great Yearning."

613
00:29:53.224 --> 00:29:55.268
"The Urge."

614
00:29:59.313 --> 00:30:01.232
So where's the tattoo?

615
00:30:02.066 --> 00:30:03.484
[Lowell]
It's coming.

616
00:30:03.609 --> 00:30:05.403
Jules still has
a few sessions to go.

617
00:30:05.570 --> 00:30:07.071
Great art takes time.

618
00:30:07.196 --> 00:30:09.282
But I promise...

619
00:30:10.324 --> 00:30:12.535
...before I leave this town...

620
00:30:13.369 --> 00:30:14.954
...she will be mine.

621
00:30:15.079 --> 00:30:16.580
[Dexter]
<i>Congrats. Lowell.</i>

622
00:30:16.581 --> 00:30:18.583
<i>You just made
the top of my list.</i>

623
00:30:18.708 --> 00:30:21.126
[Prater] You've never
had a trophy so fresh.

624
00:30:21.127 --> 00:30:23.004
Great work. Lowell.

625
00:30:23.129 --> 00:30:24.797
[sighs]

626
00:30:24.922 --> 00:30:26.089
[grunts]

627
00:30:26.090 --> 00:30:28.926
Thank you for letting us
into your process.

628
00:30:30.386 --> 00:30:31.178
Red?

629
00:30:31.179 --> 00:30:32.429
Didn't want to call you out

630
00:30:32.430 --> 00:30:33.889
your first night. but. uh.

631
00:30:33.890 --> 00:30:36.434
the money with your invitation

632
00:30:36.601 --> 00:30:38.226
was an advance
for a show and tell.

633
00:30:38.227 --> 00:30:40.646
I hope you'll feel comfortable
sharing next time.

634
00:30:40.771 --> 00:30:42.439
There'll be more of these?

635
00:30:42.440 --> 00:30:44.316
[chuckles]
Of course.

636
00:30:44.317 --> 00:30:46.777
So many events coming
in the next two weeks.

637
00:30:46.903 --> 00:30:49.113
I have so much planned.

638
00:30:49.989 --> 00:30:51.449
[Dexter]
<i>So do I.</i>

639
00:31:01.918 --> 00:31:03.920
[Angel]
<i>Ea. diablo.</i>

640
00:31:04.962 --> 00:31:06.254
Harrison?

641
00:31:06.255 --> 00:31:08.174
Harrison Morgan?

642
00:31:09.800 --> 00:31:11.259
Angel Batista.

643
00:31:11.260 --> 00:31:13.930
I used to work with your pops
in Miami Metro.

644
00:31:14.805 --> 00:31:17.308
Y... Uh. yeah. I'm-I'm sorry.
it-it d-doesn't ring a bell.

645
00:31:17.475 --> 00:31:19.643
My sister Jamie babysat you.

646
00:31:19.644 --> 00:31:21.354
Wh... Jamie?

647
00:31:21.479 --> 00:31:22.647
[chuckles softly]

648
00:31:22.813 --> 00:31:24.105
Wh... Sh...

649
00:31:24.106 --> 00:31:25.815
She used to read the hell
out of a bedtime story.

650
00:31:25.816 --> 00:31:26.942
How is she?

651
00:31:26.943 --> 00:31:28.902
Well. she finally
finished her PhD.

652
00:31:28.903 --> 00:31:31.322
She's a middle school
principal now.

653
00:31:31.447 --> 00:31:33.032
Good for her.

654
00:31:33.157 --> 00:31:34.407
Come sit. have a drink with me.

655
00:31:34.408 --> 00:31:36.160
I-I should probably clock in.

656
00:31:36.285 --> 00:31:39.080
Isn't part of your job
tending to customers?

657
00:31:41.499 --> 00:31:43.251
- Yeah. that's a good point.
- Come on.

658
00:31:44.001 --> 00:31:46.711
<i>The last time I saw you was
your fourth birthday.</i>

659
00:31:46.712 --> 00:31:49.090
I got you a red train set.

660
00:31:50.341 --> 00:31:53.134
[soft chuckle]
I loved that train set.

661
00:31:53.135 --> 00:31:54.929
So you-you were close
with my dad?

662
00:31:55.054 --> 00:31:56.846
Worked with him 20 years.

663
00:31:56.847 --> 00:31:58.598
Went through a lot together.

664
00:31:58.599 --> 00:31:59.975
- Like what?
- He was the witness

665
00:31:59.976 --> 00:32:01.351
at my wedding.

666
00:32:01.352 --> 00:32:03.854
My ex. María.
also worked at the station.

667
00:32:03.980 --> 00:32:06.065
so we had to do it on the QT

668
00:32:06.190 --> 00:32:08.067
to protect our jobs.

669
00:32:08.192 --> 00:32:10.151
Pulled your dad in
the last minute.

670
00:32:10.152 --> 00:32:12.571
Guy barely even knew
what was happening.

671
00:32:12.697 --> 00:32:14.656
[laughs. sniffles]

672
00:32:14.657 --> 00:32:16.199
Yeah. that-that sounds like him.

673
00:32:16.200 --> 00:32:18.451
Your dad is actually the reason

674
00:32:18.452 --> 00:32:21.080
I was in Iron Lake
a few weeks ago.

675
00:32:22.290 --> 00:32:24.207
S-So you heard the news?

676
00:32:24.208 --> 00:32:27.295
That he was shot and killed.

677
00:32:30.256 --> 00:32:32.591
♪ mysterious music ♪

678
00:32:32.717 --> 00:32:34.468
Sorry for your loss.

679
00:32:36.512 --> 00:32:38.805
I heard you were
in Iron Lake. too.

680
00:32:38.806 --> 00:32:40.557
- Left in a hurry.
- Yeah.

681
00:32:40.558 --> 00:32:42.560
I went up there to find my dad.

682
00:32:42.685 --> 00:32:44.895
Hadn't seen him in years.

683
00:32:46.731 --> 00:32:49.483
Turns out he wasn't
the dad I needed.

684
00:32:50.735 --> 00:32:52.902
And when everything blew up.
I split.

685
00:32:52.903 --> 00:32:55.990
Sorry Dexter wasn't the guy
you thought he was.

686
00:32:56.866 --> 00:32:59.076
I actually had
a similar experience.

687
00:32:59.201 --> 00:33:01.454
- With your dad?
- With yours.

688
00:33:06.083 --> 00:33:08.669
I'm not running into you
by chance. am I?

689
00:33:09.462 --> 00:33:12.714
Did Dexter ever share anything
about his past with you?

690
00:33:12.715 --> 00:33:14.925
About why he left Miami?

691
00:33:15.051 --> 00:33:16.676
I should probably
get back to work.

692
00:33:16.677 --> 00:33:19.346
My ex-wife had this theory.

693
00:33:19.347 --> 00:33:22.099
One that's haunted me for years.

694
00:33:23.851 --> 00:33:26.062
That your dad...

695
00:33:26.937 --> 00:33:28.439
...was the infamous
serial killer.

696
00:33:28.564 --> 00:33:30.566
the Bay Harbor Butcher.

697
00:33:32.151 --> 00:33:33.276
- What?
- I get this

698
00:33:33.277 --> 00:33:35.613
must be overwhelming.

699
00:33:35.738 --> 00:33:37.781
But if you know anything.

700
00:33:37.782 --> 00:33:40.116
you can tell me.

701
00:33:40.117 --> 00:33:41.534
Your dad's gone.

702
00:33:41.535 --> 00:33:44.038
Nothing you say can hurt him.

703
00:33:45.164 --> 00:33:46.624
I don't know
what you're talking about.

704
00:33:46.749 --> 00:33:47.833
Please.

705
00:33:47.958 --> 00:33:50.294
I need the closure.

706
00:33:52.797 --> 00:33:54.422
I wish I could help.

707
00:33:54.423 --> 00:33:55.590
Good luck.

708
00:33:55.591 --> 00:33:57.343
I'm in the city a few more days

709
00:33:57.468 --> 00:33:59.970
if you want to talk.

710
00:34:07.728 --> 00:34:09.020
[laughs]

711
00:34:09.021 --> 00:34:11.816
Still got to work
on that customer service face.

712
00:34:21.033 --> 00:34:23.661
Excuse me.
but if you think Harrison had

713
00:34:23.828 --> 00:34:25.579
anything to do
with that murder...

714
00:34:27.164 --> 00:34:28.332
What murder?

715
00:34:28.457 --> 00:34:29.874
Ryan Foster.

716
00:34:29.875 --> 00:34:31.460
He stayed here.

717
00:34:32.253 --> 00:34:34.046
The-the guy who was found
chopped up in garbage bags

718
00:34:34.171 --> 00:34:35.881
by the trash docks.

719
00:34:38.300 --> 00:34:40.010
[Al] Ah. if I could get
this thing to work.

720
00:34:40.177 --> 00:34:43.054
And it's sideways.
there we go. there she is.

721
00:34:43.055 --> 00:34:44.347
Mm.

722
00:34:44.348 --> 00:34:46.767
Yep. yep. we had our sweet

723
00:34:46.892 --> 00:34:49.478
angel Mabel.

724
00:34:49.603 --> 00:34:51.813
sweet angel. last July.

725
00:34:51.814 --> 00:34:53.983
Yeah. it's been a gift each day.

726
00:34:54.108 --> 00:34:55.276
Caught you.

727
00:34:56.318 --> 00:34:57.611
Sorry. I was just. um...

728
00:34:57.736 --> 00:34:59.572
Internet-stalking me?

729
00:34:59.697 --> 00:35:00.906
It's cool.

730
00:35:01.073 --> 00:35:03.075
I tried looking you up as well.

731
00:35:03.200 --> 00:35:04.326
You did?

732
00:35:04.452 --> 00:35:06.077
Didn't find anything.

733
00:35:06.078 --> 00:35:07.163
So mysterious.

734
00:35:07.288 --> 00:35:08.372
It's annoying. right?

735
00:35:08.497 --> 00:35:09.581
Very.

736
00:35:09.582 --> 00:35:11.416
Top me off.

737
00:35:11.417 --> 00:35:13.543
Ms. Sum-ah-lee-air?

738
00:35:13.544 --> 00:35:17.047
[chuckles]

739
00:35:17.173 --> 00:35:18.798
Perfect.

740
00:35:18.799 --> 00:35:21.093
[pours wine]

741
00:35:21.218 --> 00:35:23.929
Ooh. someone got new ink.

742
00:35:24.054 --> 00:35:25.388
[gasping]

743
00:35:25.389 --> 00:35:27.433
I'm not
one of your pervy art pieces.

744
00:35:27.558 --> 00:35:31.312
Okay. okay. Okay. okay.

745
00:35:32.229 --> 00:35:33.855
Careful with this one. Red.

746
00:35:33.856 --> 00:35:35.816
[Al] I... That's why I take
my anger out for a drive...

747
00:35:35.941 --> 00:35:39.612
Lowell needs to learn
about boundaries.

748
00:35:39.737 --> 00:35:42.448
You're an effective teacher.

749
00:35:44.074 --> 00:35:45.576
So...

750
00:35:46.452 --> 00:35:49.579
...what is your origin story?

751
00:35:49.580 --> 00:35:51.749
- [sighs]
- Let me guess.

752
00:35:51.874 --> 00:35:53.792
Terrible mother?

753
00:35:53.918 --> 00:35:56.085
I actually had a great mom.

754
00:35:56.086 --> 00:35:57.880
Interesting.

755
00:35:58.005 --> 00:36:01.132
I assumed mommy issues were
a given in this crew.

756
00:36:01.133 --> 00:36:02.675
[chuckles softly]

757
00:36:02.676 --> 00:36:04.636
Take one guess
how Al's mother wore her hair.

758
00:36:04.637 --> 00:36:05.678
[Al]
How many is that for you?

759
00:36:05.679 --> 00:36:07.014
- [Lowell] Glasses?
- Yeah.

760
00:36:07.139 --> 00:36:08.765
- [Lowell] Four.
- [Al] I count six.

761
00:36:08.766 --> 00:36:10.142
I'm not immune to mommy issues.

762
00:36:10.267 --> 00:36:12.978
Mine just come
from how I lost her.

763
00:36:13.103 --> 00:36:15.981
[sighs deeply]

764
00:36:16.982 --> 00:36:18.901
[whispers]
What is all this?

765
00:36:19.026 --> 00:36:21.778
You mean. besides the money
and the bougie wine?

766
00:36:21.779 --> 00:36:24.156
What is Prater
getting out of it?

767
00:36:25.491 --> 00:36:27.617
How about we talk tomorrow?

768
00:36:27.618 --> 00:36:28.827
Just the two of us?

769
00:36:28.953 --> 00:36:30.371
I could do that.

770
00:36:31.121 --> 00:36:32.956
Phones so you can

771
00:36:32.957 --> 00:36:35.625
communicate with the group
over the next two weeks.

772
00:36:35.626 --> 00:36:37.836
- Hat.
- Thank you.

773
00:36:37.962 --> 00:36:39.045
[Prater]
Thank you. everyone.

774
00:36:39.046 --> 00:36:40.881
for joining me this evening.

775
00:36:41.006 --> 00:36:42.549
It's been lovely catching up.

776
00:36:42.550 --> 00:36:46.344
Charley will be in touch
regarding our next gathering.

777
00:36:46.345 --> 00:36:48.304
And in the meantime.

778
00:36:48.305 --> 00:36:49.806
go and enjoy the city.

779
00:36:49.807 --> 00:36:51.475
It has so much to offer.

780
00:36:51.600 --> 00:36:53.394
Hey. you know what. I'm gonna
start a group chat so we can.

781
00:36:53.519 --> 00:36:55.520
uh. stay in touch. maybe.
maybe get a tour

782
00:36:55.521 --> 00:36:57.481
of Ellis Island
or something. huh? Yeah.

783
00:36:57.606 --> 00:36:58.649
Sound good?

784
00:36:58.774 --> 00:36:59.983
Thank you.

785
00:36:59.984 --> 00:37:01.360
See you.

786
00:37:02.778 --> 00:37:05.072
It was nice meeting you.

787
00:37:06.073 --> 00:37:08.033
Text me.

788
00:37:08.993 --> 00:37:11.245
By next meeting. a trophy.

789
00:37:11.370 --> 00:37:13.122
[chuckles]

790
00:37:15.416 --> 00:37:17.001
Bye.

791
00:37:19.878 --> 00:37:23.966
Uh... thank you.

792
00:37:24.091 --> 00:37:25.508
For everything.

793
00:37:25.509 --> 00:37:27.261
I...

794
00:37:27.386 --> 00:37:29.430
said things tonight
that I've never been able

795
00:37:29.555 --> 00:37:31.389
to express out loud before.

796
00:37:31.390 --> 00:37:33.349
Well. that's what
these gatherings are for.

797
00:37:33.350 --> 00:37:35.518
So people like you know
you're not alone.

798
00:37:35.519 --> 00:37:38.063
I didn't realize
it was something I needed.

799
00:37:38.188 --> 00:37:41.024
There's a lot of power
in sharing your story.

800
00:37:41.025 --> 00:37:44.028
Just wait
for your show-and-tell.

801
00:37:45.029 --> 00:37:46.404
Yeah. about that.

802
00:37:46.405 --> 00:37:49.032
Do I need to make
a whole presentation?

803
00:37:49.033 --> 00:37:51.326
Oh. no. nothing so elaborate.

804
00:37:51.327 --> 00:37:54.580
We just want to know
the real Dark Passenger.

805
00:37:54.705 --> 00:37:56.915
That raw animal aggression
it takes

806
00:37:57.041 --> 00:37:59.793
to saw another man's head off.

807
00:38:02.379 --> 00:38:04.632
Right.

808
00:38:06.759 --> 00:38:09.719
I'm sure you'll come up
with something great.

809
00:38:09.720 --> 00:38:11.805
Looking forward to it.

810
00:38:23.233 --> 00:38:26.362
That went exceptionally well.
don't you think?

811
00:38:26.487 --> 00:38:28.822
If you say so.

812
00:38:32.242 --> 00:38:34.828
[Dexter] <i>I've always considered
myself a lone wolf.</i>

813
00:38:34.953 --> 00:38:37.164
<i>Howling into the void.</i>

814
00:38:37.289 --> 00:38:39.083
<i>But after tonight...</i>

815
00:38:39.208 --> 00:38:41.793
<i>I can hear others
howling back to me.</i>

816
00:38:41.794 --> 00:38:44.088
- One chili dog. please.
- You got it.

817
00:38:44.213 --> 00:38:46.214
- Actually. make it two.
- Mm-hmm.

818
00:38:46.215 --> 00:38:48.509
[indistinct chatter]

819
00:38:50.678 --> 00:38:52.178
- There you go.
- Enjoy.

820
00:38:52.179 --> 00:38:53.805
Thanks.

821
00:38:53.806 --> 00:38:56.350
♪ contemplative music ♪

822
00:39:00.145 --> 00:39:02.439
[Dexter]
<i>How does the charity gala guy</i>

823
00:39:02.564 --> 00:39:05.191
<i>still do what he does
with all of us?</i>

824
00:39:05.192 --> 00:39:07.403
<i>Busy man.</i>

825
00:39:10.114 --> 00:39:12.199
[ticking]

826
00:39:15.786 --> 00:39:17.245
[ticking stops]

827
00:39:17.246 --> 00:39:19.790
[ticking resumes]

828
00:39:28.632 --> 00:39:30.384
[ticking stops]

829
00:39:31.343 --> 00:39:33.679
- [ticking resumes]
- ♪ haunting music ♪

830
00:39:40.936 --> 00:39:42.688
[door creaks open]

831
00:39:42.813 --> 00:39:44.898
[door closes]

832
00:39:46.275 --> 00:39:47.525
Everything okay?

833
00:39:47.526 --> 00:39:49.903
I think I just need
to be around a friend.

834
00:39:50.028 --> 00:39:51.864
Uh. yeah.

835
00:39:55.701 --> 00:39:59.287
[festive music playing faintly]

836
00:39:59.288 --> 00:40:02.166
[lively chatter and laughter]

837
00:40:06.587 --> 00:40:08.046
[Blessing]
Hopscotch.

838
00:40:08.172 --> 00:40:09.464
- Oh. uh...
- Butterscotch.

839
00:40:09.465 --> 00:40:11.550
[Dexter]
<i>These are good people.</i>

840
00:40:12.468 --> 00:40:14.720
<i>But they're not my people.</i>

841
00:40:20.893 --> 00:40:23.437
♪ contemplative music ♪

842
00:40:27.232 --> 00:40:29.067
[woman shouting indistinctly]

843
00:40:29.193 --> 00:40:31.403
[all cheering]

844
00:40:32.446 --> 00:40:34.573
[text alert whooshes]

845
00:40:38.243 --> 00:40:41.038
[Dexter] <i>I've run
to and from serial killers.</i>

846
00:40:41.163 --> 00:40:43.791
<i>Never with one.</i>

847
00:40:53.717 --> 00:40:55.718
It is crazy how one hair flip

848
00:40:55.719 --> 00:40:58.721
will. will make up
for a bad lip sync.

849
00:40:58.722 --> 00:41:00.140
Mm. that was a tame one.

850
00:41:00.265 --> 00:41:01.558
Just wait till somebody
pulls out the splits.

851
00:41:01.683 --> 00:41:02.935
[laughs]
Mm-mm.

852
00:41:03.060 --> 00:41:05.269
[laughs]

853
00:41:05.270 --> 00:41:07.438
Mm. I should...

854
00:41:07.439 --> 00:41:09.065
I should probably head out.
Um...

855
00:41:09.066 --> 00:41:10.776
I don't want to fall asleep
on the train again.

856
00:41:10.901 --> 00:41:12.401
The trains are
so janky this late.

857
00:41:12.402 --> 00:41:14.362
Do you want to just crash
on the couch?

858
00:41:14.363 --> 00:41:16.031
You sure?

859
00:41:16.156 --> 00:41:21.328
Yeah. Yeah. yeah. thanks.

860
00:41:22.204 --> 00:41:24.206
[chuckles softly]

861
00:41:25.207 --> 00:41:27.792
You always make me feel
really at home here.

862
00:41:27.793 --> 00:41:29.752
You're always welcome.

863
00:41:29.753 --> 00:41:31.338
I mean it.

864
00:41:33.715 --> 00:41:34.800
Harrison.

865
00:41:34.925 --> 00:41:36.176
- I. no. um...
- Fuck. Oh. my God.

866
00:41:36.301 --> 00:41:37.885
- I'm so sorry. um...
- No. no. don't be.

867
00:41:37.886 --> 00:41:39.638
- Fuck.
- We're friends. and you are

868
00:41:39.805 --> 00:41:41.222
a really great guy.
but I know you're going

869
00:41:41.223 --> 00:41:42.932
- through something.
- I'm an idiot. and. um...

870
00:41:42.933 --> 00:41:43.934
- And I'm really sorry. and I...
- And I-I got to go.

871
00:41:44.101 --> 00:41:45.434
No. I... Fuck.

872
00:41:45.435 --> 00:41:47.479
- [sighs]
- [door opens. slams]

873
00:41:47.604 --> 00:41:48.772
Fuck.

874
00:41:49.565 --> 00:41:51.941
["She's Leaving You"
by MJ Lenderman playing faintly]

875
00:41:51.942 --> 00:41:54.360
<i>♪ It falls apart ♪</i>

876
00:41:54.361 --> 00:41:56.612
<i>♪ We all got work to do ♪</i>

877
00:41:56.613 --> 00:41:59.199
I fuck everything up.

878
00:41:59.324 --> 00:42:03.244
- <i>♪ She's leaving ♪</i>
- <i>♪ It falls apart ♪</i>

879
00:42:03.245 --> 00:42:05.873
- <i>♪ We all got work to do ♪</i>
- <i>♪ You ♪</i>

880
00:42:05.998 --> 00:42:08.541
- Hi. How are you?
- I'm good. Thank you very much.

881
00:42:08.542 --> 00:42:10.544
<i>♪ She's leaving ♪</i>

882
00:42:10.669 --> 00:42:11.961
Thank you.

883
00:42:11.962 --> 00:42:13.796
Have a good day.

884
00:42:13.797 --> 00:42:16.300
<i>♪ You ♪</i>

885
00:42:17.801 --> 00:42:19.386
[Harry]
<i>He looks tired.</i>

886
00:42:20.762 --> 00:42:22.347
He's smiling.

887
00:42:22.472 --> 00:42:25.433
He was probably out late
with his friends last night.

888
00:42:25.434 --> 00:42:26.768
How would you know?

889
00:42:26.894 --> 00:42:28.979
You were too busy
being out with yours.

890
00:42:29.104 --> 00:42:30.605
[Dexter]
Give me a break.

891
00:42:30.606 --> 00:42:33.358
The last time I was at a dinner
party was at my wedding.

892
00:42:34.234 --> 00:42:36.986
I can't take care of my son
if I don't take care of myself.

893
00:42:36.987 --> 00:42:40.282
So now you're getting life
advice from ponytail trophy guy?

894
00:42:40.407 --> 00:42:42.408
Dex. if you want
real connection.

895
00:42:42.409 --> 00:42:44.620
that's where
you should be looking.

896
00:42:44.745 --> 00:42:46.495
Yeah. I tried.

897
00:42:46.496 --> 00:42:48.248
He shot me.

898
00:42:49.166 --> 00:42:50.583
Never thought
I'd get another chance

899
00:42:50.584 --> 00:42:53.502
to be open
with someone like that.

900
00:42:53.503 --> 00:42:55.255
Until last night.

901
00:42:56.173 --> 00:42:58.257
Those aren't your friends.

902
00:42:58.258 --> 00:43:00.217
They're supposed
to be your victims.

903
00:43:00.218 --> 00:43:02.554
I'm gonna do it. Dad.
I'm just being smart about it.

904
00:43:02.679 --> 00:43:04.306
Smart or stalling

905
00:43:04.431 --> 00:43:05.641
because you like these people?

906
00:43:05.766 --> 00:43:07.434
If they start disappearing
one by one.

907
00:43:07.559 --> 00:43:09.770
how's that gonna look
for the new guy?

908
00:43:10.604 --> 00:43:12.647
Best to wait
until the meetings are over.

909
00:43:12.648 --> 00:43:14.608
That works fine
for most of your new pals.

910
00:43:14.733 --> 00:43:16.401
But explain that to the woman
who's gonna get

911
00:43:16.568 --> 00:43:17.903
her arm de-sleeved

912
00:43:18.028 --> 00:43:19.488
before Lowell leaves town.

913
00:43:19.613 --> 00:43:21.238
- That is a complication.
- Yeah.

914
00:43:21.239 --> 00:43:23.367
And so is your date
with Lady Vengeance.

915
00:43:23.492 --> 00:43:25.118
It's not a date. it's a...

916
00:43:25.243 --> 00:43:27.412
fact-finding mission.

917
00:43:29.373 --> 00:43:31.874
I haven't forgotten
why I'm here.

918
00:43:31.875 --> 00:43:34.628
[line ringing]

919
00:43:36.129 --> 00:43:37.880
[Lowell]
<i>The fuck?</i>

920
00:43:37.881 --> 00:43:39.382
<i>It's not even 11.</i>

921
00:43:39.383 --> 00:43:41.885
Uh. sorry.
I forgot you're on vacation.

922
00:43:42.010 --> 00:43:44.470
Would you maybe want
to meet up sometime?

923
00:43:44.471 --> 00:43:46.765
Would love to hear
more about your...

924
00:43:46.890 --> 00:43:48.058
skins.

925
00:43:48.183 --> 00:43:49.768
<i>Yeah. sure.</i>

926
00:43:49.893 --> 00:43:51.394
<i>I'm not much of a day guy.</i>

927
00:43:51.395 --> 00:43:53.854
<i>- so can we say happy hour?</i>
- Perfect.

928
00:43:53.855 --> 00:43:55.482
- Just text me where to...
- [line clicks]

929
00:43:57.484 --> 00:43:59.319
See?

930
00:43:59.444 --> 00:44:01.947
And I still have time
to fit in a jog.

931
00:44:05.534 --> 00:44:06.994
So. you run every day?

932
00:44:07.119 --> 00:44:08.452
Got to stay in shape.

933
00:44:08.453 --> 00:44:09.997
Not all of us get
to do our thing

934
00:44:10.122 --> 00:44:12.499
by sitting
in the backseat of a car.

935
00:44:12.624 --> 00:44:15.084
So. when's a good time
to talk about Prater?

936
00:44:15.085 --> 00:44:16.752
Fire away.

937
00:44:16.753 --> 00:44:18.045
I'll answer any questions

938
00:44:18.046 --> 00:44:20.256
- for as long as you can keep up.
- [chuckles]

939
00:44:20.257 --> 00:44:23.092
How many of Prater's gatherings
have you been to?

940
00:44:23.093 --> 00:44:25.052
This is my fourth year.

941
00:44:25.053 --> 00:44:27.014
But they started
a few years before that.

942
00:44:27.139 --> 00:44:29.140
Four years? You must enjoy it.

943
00:44:29.141 --> 00:44:31.684
I enjoy the money.

944
00:44:31.685 --> 00:44:34.186
Is Prater really just a fan?

945
00:44:34.187 --> 00:44:36.230
I mean. the guy's a voyeur.

946
00:44:36.231 --> 00:44:37.566
He's a vampire.

947
00:44:37.691 --> 00:44:40.027
He wants all the dirty details.

948
00:44:40.152 --> 00:44:43.196
But. no. I don't think
he's actually a killer himself.

949
00:44:43.321 --> 00:44:44.823
Do you want a water?

950
00:44:44.948 --> 00:44:46.575
I want a water.

951
00:44:46.700 --> 00:44:47.701
Two waters.

952
00:44:47.826 --> 00:44:49.327
Six dollars.

953
00:44:49.453 --> 00:44:50.411
Thanks.

954
00:44:50.412 --> 00:44:51.371
Thank you.

955
00:44:51.496 --> 00:44:53.040
And there's really no catch?

956
00:44:53.165 --> 00:44:56.584
As long as you don't break
any of his rules.

957
00:44:56.585 --> 00:44:57.835
Mm.

958
00:44:57.836 --> 00:44:59.880
So. breaking rules.

959
00:45:01.006 --> 00:45:02.673
Is that what happened
with that Keith guy

960
00:45:02.674 --> 00:45:04.884
- Prater was talking about?
- Yep.

961
00:45:04.885 --> 00:45:07.721
It appears the Canton Clubber

962
00:45:07.846 --> 00:45:09.139
is no more.

963
00:45:09.264 --> 00:45:11.640
That happen often.
people breaking rules?

964
00:45:11.641 --> 00:45:13.642
Well. not everybody
gets invited back.

965
00:45:13.643 --> 00:45:15.228
if that's what you're asking.

966
00:45:15.353 --> 00:45:17.480
One guy got uninvited.

967
00:45:17.481 --> 00:45:19.024
Another got arrested.

968
00:45:19.191 --> 00:45:21.358
And then
his first night in jail.

969
00:45:21.359 --> 00:45:23.320
he committed suicide.

970
00:45:23.445 --> 00:45:25.447
[whispers]
Allegedly.

971
00:45:28.241 --> 00:45:29.784
So...

972
00:45:29.785 --> 00:45:32.079
where'd you grow up?

973
00:45:35.207 --> 00:45:36.917
All over.

974
00:45:37.751 --> 00:45:40.587
Mom was always looking
for something new.

975
00:45:40.712 --> 00:45:42.089
Someone new.

976
00:45:42.214 --> 00:45:44.632
The longest stay was in Tulsa.

977
00:45:44.633 --> 00:45:46.259
Mm.

978
00:45:46.384 --> 00:45:47.718
I drove through there once.

979
00:45:47.719 --> 00:45:50.930
Then you know
there's shit-all to do.

980
00:45:50.931 --> 00:45:53.391
Not that I gave it a chance.

981
00:45:55.143 --> 00:45:57.354
I was a loner.

982
00:45:58.897 --> 00:46:01.441
Other than my younger sister
Hazel.

983
00:46:02.692 --> 00:46:04.611
She was an angel.

984
00:46:04.736 --> 00:46:06.487
I...

985
00:46:06.488 --> 00:46:08.239
was...

986
00:46:08.240 --> 00:46:09.741
not.

987
00:46:10.742 --> 00:46:13.161
When did you know you were...

988
00:46:15.247 --> 00:46:17.541
...different?

989
00:46:18.542 --> 00:46:20.669
Always.

990
00:46:21.419 --> 00:46:24.047
In the first grade
there was this bowl-cut kid

991
00:46:24.172 --> 00:46:25.507
who annoyed me.

992
00:46:25.632 --> 00:46:28.008
so I hit him in the head
with my library book

993
00:46:28.009 --> 00:46:30.929
and I stuck thumbtacks
into his face.

994
00:46:31.054 --> 00:46:33.764
If I had normal parents
who believed in therapy.

995
00:46:33.765 --> 00:46:35.558
maybe I would have been
diagnosed

996
00:46:35.559 --> 00:46:37.894
with some fancy
personality disorder.

997
00:46:38.019 --> 00:46:41.398
Instead. they told me to "stop
being so angry all the time."

998
00:46:43.817 --> 00:46:47.028
I almost stabbed a kid
on a basketball court once.

999
00:46:48.113 --> 00:46:49.990
My dad stopped me.

1000
00:46:52.576 --> 00:46:54.118
He tried to help.

1001
00:46:54.119 --> 00:46:56.329
Best he could.

1002
00:47:00.792 --> 00:47:03.628
When I was 15. I found ballet.

1003
00:47:03.753 --> 00:47:05.922
It is a punishing practice.

1004
00:47:06.047 --> 00:47:09.009
Gave me a release
for all that pent-up rage.

1005
00:47:09.134 --> 00:47:10.467
And I was good enough

1006
00:47:10.468 --> 00:47:13.762
that I got into a dance academy
out of town.

1007
00:47:13.763 --> 00:47:16.474
Away from my mother's
new boyfriend.

1008
00:47:17.642 --> 00:47:20.187
The way that creep looked at me.

1009
00:47:21.396 --> 00:47:23.063
But you got out of there.

1010
00:47:23.064 --> 00:47:25.025
I did.

1011
00:47:26.193 --> 00:47:28.612
Hazel didn't.

1012
00:47:29.613 --> 00:47:32.157
I thought she was too young.

1013
00:47:32.949 --> 00:47:35.243
And when I came back
for the summer.

1014
00:47:35.368 --> 00:47:37.829
I found out.

1015
00:47:37.996 --> 00:47:39.831
And I killed the guy.

1016
00:47:40.665 --> 00:47:42.375
And I got to tell you.

1017
00:47:43.251 --> 00:47:45.837
Much better release
than the ballet.

1018
00:47:48.215 --> 00:47:51.051
I'll never forget
how my first time felt.

1019
00:47:52.677 --> 00:47:57.057
Like a path
had finally opened up for me.

1020
00:48:01.061 --> 00:48:02.561
Are you hungry?

1021
00:48:02.562 --> 00:48:05.314
- Always.
- My Airbnb is a few blocks away.

1022
00:48:05.315 --> 00:48:06.941
Do you want to come over?

1023
00:48:06.942 --> 00:48:09.568
[sighs]

1024
00:48:09.569 --> 00:48:10.820
I'd love to. but...

1025
00:48:10.987 --> 00:48:12.906
Come on.

1026
00:48:13.740 --> 00:48:15.408
I have incredible pastries.

1027
00:48:15.533 --> 00:48:19.079
And I love a good reward
after the end of a run.

1028
00:48:37.389 --> 00:48:40.433
Oh. this is the vegan one.

1029
00:48:40.558 --> 00:48:42.102
It's kale.

1030
00:48:42.227 --> 00:48:45.146
Thanks for remembering.

1031
00:48:58.493 --> 00:49:00.787
Did this come with the place?

1032
00:49:02.539 --> 00:49:04.374
See for yourself.

1033
00:49:04.499 --> 00:49:07.294
♪ intriguing music ♪

1034
00:49:19.055 --> 00:49:20.889
[exhales]

1035
00:49:20.890 --> 00:49:21.932
Is this...

1036
00:49:21.933 --> 00:49:23.935
My collection.

1037
00:49:28.481 --> 00:49:31.608
I can still remember
all of their faces.

1038
00:49:31.609 --> 00:49:34.320
The look in their eyes
right before I killed them.

1039
00:49:34.321 --> 00:49:36.405
[exhales]

1040
00:49:36.406 --> 00:49:38.491
It's nice.

1041
00:49:39.534 --> 00:49:41.995
Being able to remember.

1042
00:49:46.207 --> 00:49:48.042
I...

1043
00:49:48.043 --> 00:49:50.628
I'm gonna take a quick shower.

1044
00:49:50.754 --> 00:49:52.296
Okay.

1045
00:49:52.297 --> 00:49:55.467
There's an Italian espresso
maker in the kitchen.

1046
00:49:56.885 --> 00:49:58.635
Help yourself.

1047
00:49:58.636 --> 00:50:00.596
Okay.

1048
00:50:00.597 --> 00:50:02.849
[sighs]

1049
00:50:05.185 --> 00:50:07.187
[door opens]

1050
00:50:18.448 --> 00:50:20.575
[exhales]

1051
00:50:24.245 --> 00:50:26.373
Showering with a serial killer?

1052
00:50:26.498 --> 00:50:27.915
[water running]

1053
00:50:27.916 --> 00:50:30.752
Not exactly part of the Code.

1054
00:50:31.669 --> 00:50:34.089
Remember happy hour with Lowell.

1055
00:50:34.214 --> 00:50:35.382
[sighs]

1056
00:50:37.175 --> 00:50:38.801
Uh. something just came up.

1057
00:50:38.802 --> 00:50:40.553
[Mia]
What?

1058
00:50:42.013 --> 00:50:44.224
Thanks for the run.

1059
00:50:45.683 --> 00:50:47.936
[mellow rock music
playing over stereo]

1060
00:50:55.235 --> 00:50:56.069
Hey.

1061
00:50:56.194 --> 00:50:57.570
Sorry I'm late.

1062
00:50:58.363 --> 00:50:59.906
Next round's on me.

1063
00:51:00.031 --> 00:51:01.366
- What are you drinking?
- Yo. can I take a rain check?

1064
00:51:01.491 --> 00:51:02.366
I kinda got to...

1065
00:51:02.367 --> 00:51:04.577
- get ready.
- For what?

1066
00:51:07.872 --> 00:51:09.164
[Lowell]
I thought it'd take

1067
00:51:09.165 --> 00:51:12.627
more sessions.
but her pain tolerance is crazy.

1068
00:51:12.752 --> 00:51:14.170
You mean...

1069
00:51:14.295 --> 00:51:15.130
Yep.

1070
00:51:15.255 --> 00:51:18.590
Tonight's the night. baby.

1071
00:51:18.591 --> 00:51:21.218
Good thing I came prepared.

1072
00:51:21.219 --> 00:51:23.346
Check it out.

1073
00:51:24.681 --> 00:51:27.600
My day job's anesthesiology.

1074
00:51:27.725 --> 00:51:30.270
But it helps
in my nightlife. too.

1075
00:51:32.397 --> 00:51:33.856
My next piece will be ready

1076
00:51:33.857 --> 00:51:35.232
in about two hours.

1077
00:51:35.233 --> 00:51:37.651
And then she'll be walking
back to her place

1078
00:51:37.652 --> 00:51:39.362
a few blocks away.

1079
00:51:39.487 --> 00:51:41.197
In the dark.

1080
00:51:41.322 --> 00:51:43.240
So. if you'll excuse me.

1081
00:51:43.241 --> 00:51:45.200
I kinda have to get in the zone.

1082
00:51:45.201 --> 00:51:47.119
I love talking shop. but...

1083
00:51:47.120 --> 00:51:48.996
this next piece is more
of a "me" thing

1084
00:51:48.997 --> 00:51:50.248
than a "we" thing.

1085
00:51:50.415 --> 00:51:52.082
- You get it.
- Uh. yeah.

1086
00:51:52.083 --> 00:51:55.128
I couldn't imagine doing this
with someone else.

1087
00:51:56.045 --> 00:51:57.839
[Lowell sighs]

1088
00:52:03.845 --> 00:52:05.888
[Dexter]
<i>Shit. Lowell is ready.</i>

1089
00:52:05.889 --> 00:52:07.307
<i>and I'm not.</i>

1090
00:52:07.432 --> 00:52:09.851
<i>I didn't bring my tools.</i>

1091
00:52:09.976 --> 00:52:12.979
♪ thrilling music ♪

1092
00:52:18.818 --> 00:52:21.154
<i>Great.
it'll only take me two hours</i>

1093
00:52:21.279 --> 00:52:22.654
<i>to get to Queens.</i>

1094
00:52:22.655 --> 00:52:24.282
Fucking New York City.

1095
00:52:24.407 --> 00:52:26.743
♪ "Stayin' Alive"
by the Bee Gees playing ♪

1096
00:52:29.579 --> 00:52:32.289
<i>♪ Life goin' nowhere ♪</i>

1097
00:52:32.290 --> 00:52:34.583
<i>♪ Somebody help me ♪</i>

1098
00:52:34.584 --> 00:52:38.171
- [knocking]
- <i>♪ Somebody help me. yeah ♪</i>

1099
00:52:38.421 --> 00:52:41.173
♪

1100
00:52:41.174 --> 00:52:43.175
<i>♪ Life goin' nowhere... ♪</i>

1101
00:52:43.176 --> 00:52:44.761
Still stuck on Harrison Morgan?

1102
00:52:44.886 --> 00:52:46.804
Sleeping at the hotel
where the crime took place.

1103
00:52:46.930 --> 00:52:48.263
Hardly an alibi.

1104
00:52:48.264 --> 00:52:49.473
You really think a kid
that young is capable

1105
00:52:49.474 --> 00:52:51.184
of a crime that sophisticated?

1106
00:52:51.309 --> 00:52:53.602
I will admit it is unlikely.

1107
00:52:53.603 --> 00:52:55.647
We must be missing something.

1108
00:52:55.772 --> 00:52:57.898
I just need to take a step back. recalibrate.

1109
00:52:57.899 --> 00:53:00.567
Start from the top
and look at everything anew.

1110
00:53:00.568 --> 00:53:03.363
[sighs]

1111
00:53:04.572 --> 00:53:07.367
I've seen you fixate
like this before.

1112
00:53:09.327 --> 00:53:10.911
It almost cost you your job.

1113
00:53:10.912 --> 00:53:13.248
Claude. please don't make this

1114
00:53:13.373 --> 00:53:14.623
another New York Ripper.

1115
00:53:14.624 --> 00:53:16.417
I have no plans to obsess.

1116
00:53:16.543 --> 00:53:18.294
Balance is important.

1117
00:53:18.419 --> 00:53:21.214
In fact. I have taken on
an extracurricular endeavor.

1118
00:53:21.381 --> 00:53:23.340
A series
of speaking engagements.

1119
00:53:23.341 --> 00:53:25.050
Oh. yeah? What about?

1120
00:53:25.051 --> 00:53:27.136
The New York Ripper.

1121
00:53:29.514 --> 00:53:31.766
[Angel]
Detective Wallace?

1122
00:53:32.684 --> 00:53:34.060
How can we help you?

1123
00:53:34.185 --> 00:53:36.103
Angel Batista. Miami Homicide.

1124
00:53:36.104 --> 00:53:37.730
I heard about the body you found

1125
00:53:37.897 --> 00:53:39.106
cut into nine pieces.

1126
00:53:39.107 --> 00:53:40.775
I once worked a case in Miami

1127
00:53:40.900 --> 00:53:42.150
that was eerily similar.

1128
00:53:42.151 --> 00:53:44.821
Was never sure we caught
the right guy.

1129
00:53:45.572 --> 00:53:47.282
You mind if I pick your brain
a minute?

1130
00:53:47.407 --> 00:53:50.201
♪ intriguing music ♪

1131
00:53:50.326 --> 00:53:51.994
How much time do you have?

1132
00:53:51.995 --> 00:53:54.414
As much
as you're willing to give.

1133
00:54:02.046 --> 00:54:04.090
♪ "They Want Blood"
by Dogmuscle playing ♪

1134
00:54:04.215 --> 00:54:07.217
<i>♪ Your cover's a grave ♪</i>

1135
00:54:07.218 --> 00:54:10.220
<i>♪ Defending only cemeteries ♪</i>

1136
00:54:10.221 --> 00:54:12.473
<i>♪ War. blood. gore.
dear God... ♪</i>

1137
00:54:12.599 --> 00:54:14.851
[song continues faintly
over headphones]

1138
00:54:26.696 --> 00:54:29.115
[gas hissing]

1139
00:54:33.661 --> 00:54:35.455
[grunts]

1140
00:54:37.290 --> 00:54:39.667
Count backward from one.

1141
00:54:41.085 --> 00:54:43.421
♪ menacing music ♪

1142
00:55:00.021 --> 00:55:04.609
[Dexter] <i>Tattoo parlors really
do have everything I need.</i>

1143
00:55:07.779 --> 00:55:09.446
<i>And lucky for me.</i>

1144
00:55:09.447 --> 00:55:12.992
<i>Lowell brought everything else.</i>

1145
00:55:20.583 --> 00:55:24.003
<i>Harry thought my trophies
were disgusting.</i>

1146
00:55:26.214 --> 00:55:27.340
<i>He couldn't understand.</i>

1147
00:55:27.465 --> 00:55:30.343
<i>He wasn't like me.</i>

1148
00:55:35.807 --> 00:55:37.517
<i>Like us.</i>

1149
00:55:40.853 --> 00:55:43.398
[sniffling]

1150
00:55:45.775 --> 00:55:47.819
[Lowell panting]

1151
00:55:49.445 --> 00:55:51.114
[sighs]

1152
00:55:51.239 --> 00:55:52.865
Fuck me.

1153
00:55:53.032 --> 00:55:55.535
You were right about one thing.

1154
00:55:55.660 --> 00:55:58.579
Tonight's the night. baby.

1155
00:55:59.330 --> 00:56:03.960
You're gonna fuck with Prater's
rules after day one.

1156
00:56:04.085 --> 00:56:06.629
[laughs]
Whoa. ballsy.

1157
00:56:06.754 --> 00:56:08.381
I'll take my chances.

1158
00:56:08.506 --> 00:56:11.092
[sighs]

1159
00:56:12.260 --> 00:56:14.553
This is usually the part
where people start screaming

1160
00:56:14.554 --> 00:56:15.972
and begging for their lives.

1161
00:56:16.097 --> 00:56:18.473
Yeah. well.
I've been on the other side

1162
00:56:18.474 --> 00:56:21.351
of this long enough
to know when it's inevitable.

1163
00:56:21.352 --> 00:56:24.063
Sorry to droop your chub.

1164
00:56:24.188 --> 00:56:25.772
[chuckles]

1165
00:56:25.773 --> 00:56:29.068
Could you at least do me a solid
and knock me out first?

1166
00:56:30.445 --> 00:56:31.863
No.

1167
00:56:36.868 --> 00:56:39.454
Why do you keep the skins?

1168
00:56:41.789 --> 00:56:44.124
I like looking at 'em

1169
00:56:44.125 --> 00:56:47.753
when that pressure
starts building.

1170
00:56:47.754 --> 00:56:49.756
They...

1171
00:56:49.881 --> 00:56:51.841
calm me.

1172
00:56:53.009 --> 00:56:55.552
If I didn't have my skins.

1173
00:56:55.553 --> 00:56:57.554
I'd have killed
a lot more often.

1174
00:56:57.555 --> 00:57:00.474
Got sloppy. got caught.

1175
00:57:00.475 --> 00:57:02.768
Damn.

1176
00:57:02.769 --> 00:57:04.771
I'm gonna miss 'em.

1177
00:57:07.899 --> 00:57:10.568
I know how you feel.

1178
00:57:14.572 --> 00:57:16.908
♪ haunting music ♪

1179
00:57:27.919 --> 00:57:30.963
That's why I'm going
back to basics.

1180
00:57:49.941 --> 00:57:52.734
That's your trophy?

1181
00:57:52.735 --> 00:57:54.529
[scoffs]
Pretty lame

1182
00:57:54.654 --> 00:57:57.156
for someone who saws off heads.

1183
00:57:58.407 --> 00:58:00.868
[sighs]

1184
00:58:05.289 --> 00:58:08.167
There's one thing I couldn't be
honest about last night.

1185
00:58:08.292 --> 00:58:09.585
Is that right?

1186
00:58:09.710 --> 00:58:12.380
I'm not Ronald Schmidt.

1187
00:58:14.966 --> 00:58:17.051
I'm Dexter Morgan.

1188
00:58:17.176 --> 00:58:18.636
Who's that?

1189
00:58:18.761 --> 00:58:21.013
The Bay Harbor Butcher.

1190
00:58:22.473 --> 00:58:25.184
Fu...!
[gasps]

1191
00:58:26.853 --> 00:58:30.314
[straining]

1192
00:58:32.066 --> 00:58:35.319
You... you...

1193
00:58:39.323 --> 00:58:41.534
♪

1194
00:58:56.674 --> 00:58:58.050
[Harry] You know.
when I first brought you home.

1195
00:58:58.175 --> 00:58:59.719
I never imagined
we'd be driving around

1196
00:58:59.844 --> 00:59:01.762
with a chopped-up body
in your trunk.

1197
00:59:01.888 --> 00:59:05.015
Yeah. I'm sorry we didn't have
the father-son relationship

1198
00:59:05.016 --> 00:59:06.391
you dreamed of.

1199
00:59:06.392 --> 00:59:08.143
How could we have?

1200
00:59:08.144 --> 00:59:09.562
You weren't like me.

1201
00:59:09.687 --> 00:59:12.856
So I had to stop worrying
about what I wanted

1202
00:59:12.857 --> 00:59:15.400
and focus on what you needed.

1203
00:59:15.401 --> 00:59:17.027
Looking back.

1204
00:59:17.028 --> 00:59:19.447
I wouldn't have it
any other way.

1205
00:59:24.035 --> 00:59:25.870
I see what you're doing here.
and you're right.

1206
00:59:25.995 --> 00:59:29.414
I'd rather have a relationship
with Harrison than...

1207
00:59:29.415 --> 00:59:30.917
the people at Prater's.

1208
00:59:31.042 --> 00:59:32.043
Then why don't you?

1209
00:59:32.168 --> 00:59:33.961
Because it's not
just my decision.

1210
00:59:34.795 --> 00:59:38.256
What if Harrison
would rather I stay dead?

1211
00:59:38.257 --> 00:59:41.177
I don't get scared. but that...

1212
00:59:41.302 --> 00:59:44.304
that scares the shit out of me.

1213
00:59:44.305 --> 00:59:46.807
Then do something about it.

1214
00:59:48.225 --> 00:59:52.104
[grunting]

1215
00:59:53.147 --> 00:59:55.691
Lowell. meet Red.

1216
01:00:01.739 --> 01:00:03.282
[Harry]
And let's talk about Lowell.

1217
01:00:03.407 --> 01:00:05.993
It'll be suspicious when he
doesn't show up at Prater's.

1218
01:00:06.118 --> 01:00:08.703
Being the new guy makes you
the natural suspect.

1219
01:00:08.704 --> 01:00:12.208
Uh. weren't you the one
who told me to kill Lowell?

1220
01:00:16.170 --> 01:00:18.922
I'll figure something out.

1221
01:00:18.923 --> 01:00:20.716
This is what I'm best at.

1222
01:00:20.841 --> 01:00:23.009
[elevator bell dings]

1223
01:00:23.010 --> 01:00:25.137
[indistinct chatter]

1224
01:00:28.933 --> 01:00:30.810
Yo. Lance.

1225
01:00:33.312 --> 01:00:34.689
What's good?

1226
01:00:34.814 --> 01:00:36.649
Did you sell me a stolen truck?

1227
01:00:36.816 --> 01:00:38.651
What? N-No.

1228
01:00:38.776 --> 01:00:40.361
It was my dad's.

1229
01:00:40.486 --> 01:00:41.653
Then why'd
some fedora-ass cop show up

1230
01:00:41.654 --> 01:00:43.322
at my place the other night?

1231
01:00:44.198 --> 01:00:45.616
I. uh...

1232
01:00:45.741 --> 01:00:47.326
I-I don't know.

1233
01:00:47.451 --> 01:00:49.494
Better figure it the fuck out.

1234
01:00:49.495 --> 01:00:51.163
He's right over there.

1235
01:00:52.540 --> 01:00:54.834
♪ slow. ominous music ♪

1236
01:01:04.885 --> 01:01:07.054
How about a cup of coffee?

1237
01:01:13.602 --> 01:01:15.021
I'm guessing
you didn't come back

1238
01:01:15.146 --> 01:01:16.856
with more cute Miami stories.

1239
01:01:16.981 --> 01:01:19.191
I just heard about a guest
at your hotel.

1240
01:01:20.026 --> 01:01:21.944
You ever meet Ryan Foster?

1241
01:01:22.653 --> 01:01:24.362
Meet a lot of people at a hotel.

1242
01:01:24.363 --> 01:01:26.489
You might remember this one.

1243
01:01:26.490 --> 01:01:29.535
Came in one piece. left in nine.

1244
01:01:30.995 --> 01:01:32.663
Yeah. I saw that guy
on the news.

1245
01:01:32.788 --> 01:01:34.789
Funny thing is...

1246
01:01:34.790 --> 01:01:38.210
that's exactly the way
the Bay Harbor Butcher did it.

1247
01:01:39.962 --> 01:01:42.630
I really hope
they catch that guy.

1248
01:01:42.631 --> 01:01:45.967
I spoke to the lead on the case.
Detective Wallace.

1249
01:01:45.968 --> 01:01:48.219
She said the cleanup
of the suspected

1250
01:01:48.220 --> 01:01:49.888
murder site was impeccable.

1251
01:01:49.889 --> 01:01:52.348
Almost as if the culprit
was an expert.

1252
01:01:52.349 --> 01:01:55.561
Or learned from one.

1253
01:01:56.353 --> 01:01:57.563
That sounds crazy.

1254
01:01:57.688 --> 01:01:59.565
Less crazy if you know the son

1255
01:01:59.690 --> 01:02:01.067
of a notorious serial killer

1256
01:02:01.192 --> 01:02:03.652
was at the same hotel
that night.

1257
01:02:04.403 --> 01:02:07.822
I didn't mention anything
about you yet.

1258
01:02:07.823 --> 01:02:09.365
And I don't have to.

1259
01:02:09.366 --> 01:02:12.494
I'm just looking
for confirmation.

1260
01:02:12.495 --> 01:02:14.580
About Dexter.

1261
01:02:15.372 --> 01:02:17.040
I already told you.

1262
01:02:17.041 --> 01:02:18.709
I don't know
what you're talking about.

1263
01:02:18.876 --> 01:02:20.711
Honestly. that guy Ryan

1264
01:02:20.878 --> 01:02:22.587
sounded like a real asshole.

1265
01:02:22.588 --> 01:02:24.006
Good riddance.

1266
01:02:24.131 --> 01:02:25.591
Did your dad make it seem

1267
01:02:25.716 --> 01:02:27.468
like that's all he was doing?

1268
01:02:28.427 --> 01:02:29.929
Taking out the worst criminals?

1269
01:02:30.054 --> 01:02:32.640
Making the world a better place?

1270
01:02:32.765 --> 01:02:35.517
Like he was
some sort of Dark Avenger?

1271
01:02:35.518 --> 01:02:37.770
A lot of innocent people died

1272
01:02:37.895 --> 01:02:39.105
because of your dad.

1273
01:02:39.230 --> 01:02:40.897
People that I loved.

1274
01:02:40.898 --> 01:02:43.608
My ex-wife María LaGuerta.
your Aunt Deb.

1275
01:02:43.609 --> 01:02:45.152
your mother.

1276
01:02:49.990 --> 01:02:53.285
Sounds like you've gone down a
real conspiratorial rabbit hole.

1277
01:02:54.120 --> 01:02:56.579
Good luck getting out of it.

1278
01:02:56.580 --> 01:02:58.290
We're done here.

1279
01:02:59.583 --> 01:03:03.045
This is a dark path
you're going down.

1280
01:03:05.756 --> 01:03:08.968
I truly hope you don't become
like your dad.

1281
01:03:09.718 --> 01:03:11.929
♪ pensive music ♪

1282
01:03:28.863 --> 01:03:31.407
[watch ticking]

1283
01:03:33.659 --> 01:03:35.243
[Angel]
<i>Did your dad make it seem</i>

1284
01:03:35.244 --> 01:03:36.619
<i>like that's all he was doing?</i>

1285
01:03:36.620 --> 01:03:40.166
<i>Like he was some sort
of Dark Avenger?</i>

1286
01:03:40.291 --> 01:03:43.793
<i>A lot of innocent people died
because of your dad.</i>

1287
01:03:43.794 --> 01:03:46.963
<i>My ex-wife María LaGuerta.
your Aunt Deb.</i>

1288
01:03:46.964 --> 01:03:48.423
<i>your mother.</i>

1289
01:03:48.424 --> 01:03:50.843
♪ haunting music ♪

1290
01:03:51.760 --> 01:03:54.763
[watch ticking slows]

1291
01:03:58.934 --> 01:04:02.229
<i>This is a dark path
you're going down.</i>

1292
